\begin_inset Formula $\delta_{J}^{K}=\mbox{\ det}\!\left(\left(\delta_{j_{1}},\dots,\delta_{j_{n-r}}\right)^{T}\left(\delta_{k_{1}},\dots,\delta_{k_{n-r}}\right)\right)$
\end_inset

 and write the above result as:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\varepsilon_{IJ}\varepsilon_{IK}=r!\,\delta_{J}^{K}
\]

\end_inset


